Tom,

Yeah, there is limited choices on rubber for 15" rims as far as I 
know. I have 15" rims on my bus. I have used michelin passenger car 
tires in the past P205-75-15's with the radial R in there somewhere. 
Currently I have Bridgestones which are no longer available in that 
size. Anyway, they don't fit all the way into the spare tire well in 
my non-walk thru causing my 2/3 passenger seat to sit forward a 
little. Fish around a bit and you should find something suitable as 
for the 4" wides, maybe those are bug rims? I'm sure mine are 5 or 
5.5".

Chris

